                            <comment id="55203" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 17:26:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The wiki page: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/opensfs/New+LFSCK+UI+Design&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/opensfs/New+LFSCK+UI+Design&lt;/a&gt; has access limited to OpenSFS PAC members (of which Cory is a member.) Once the design is agreed it is transferred into the Manual. The LFSCK UI documentation has not yet completed review for the Manual but a preliminary version is available here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual-reviews/308/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.lfsckadmin&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual-reviews/308/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.lfsckadmin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="55200" author="paf" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 17:06:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am logged in to the Whamcloud wiki, but unable to access &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/opensfs/New+LFSCK+UI+Design&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/opensfs/New+LFSCK+UI+Design&lt;/a&gt; .  I get a &quot;Page Not Found&quot; message from the wiki indicating I may not have permission to view the page (or that it does not exist).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cory Spitz from Cray can access this page, so it appears to be an issue with permissions.&lt;br/&gt;
Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
